The paper focuses on the identification of IoT devices using RF fingerprinting, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The proposed method involves modeling the physical-layer process of the devices, which requires knowledge of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The system also needs to be robust to wireless channels, which involves control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
